Yes, Wednesday still works well for me, and I think the earlier start is the better option.

If we meet around eight-thirty, we will have enough time to settle the agenda before everyone joins. I would bring the draft notes, and you can bring the printed checklist if that is still useful. Also, I agree with your point about keeping the discussion focused on the schedule first and leaving the formatting questions for the end.

For lunch, the cafe across from the library sounds fine. I checked their menu before, and there are a few simple choices that should work for everyone. If Maya cannot make it by noon, we can save the last item for a short follow-up call later in the afternoon.

Also, thanks for reminding me about the document labels. I renamed the folders so they match the latest version names and cut down the duplicates.

AAA

Roadside support information for resident driver enrollment in your area

 

You qualify for a Courtesy Roadside Kit through your local resident eligibility area

This notice is being sent because of where you live. Licensed drivers in your region may receive a Premier Roadside Support kit through the resident program, and the kit is provided at no charge to eligible residents. No payment is required for eligible recipients, and you will not be billed for the kit.

Review your AAA courtesy kit details

Premier Roadside Support is intended to help residents keep a practical set of emergency items close at hand in the vehicle. If your home address is within the supported area, this offer is covered by the program for residents in your area.

What the kit may include

Battery jumper cables

Reflective warning triangle

Compact flashlight

High-visibility safety vest

Rain poncho

Tire pressure gauge

Work gloves

Multi-use towel

Emergency contact card

Basic first-aid supplies

Vehicle window marker

Storage pouch for trunk use

Availability note: distribution follows local program allocation, so fulfillment may vary across neighborhoods within the supported area.

If you would like to review the coverage details for your residency area and confirm kit availability, use the button above to continue. Thank you for taking a moment to check your local eligibility.

We appreciate your time and your attention to regional driver support information.

 

Yes, I can help with that, and your plan makes sense if we keep the steps simple.

Start with the outline you already have and trim any repeated points before the meeting. After that, send me the second section, because that part needed the clearest wording the last time we reviewed it. I also think your idea of assigning names beside each task is helpful since it avoids confusion later.

For Thursday, let us keep the in-person session short and move the extra discussion to a call if we run over. I can bring my notebook, and I will summarize the main decisions after we finish. If Nora wants to join remotely, that is fine with me as long as she gets the updated timetable first.

One more thing: the room near the west stairwell is quieter in the morning, so I would reserve that one if it is still open.

